<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-export SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/evernote-export2.dtd">
<en-export export-date="20260629T000000Z" application="Codex" version="1">
<note><title>2026/06/17 Wed</title><content><![CDATA[<en-note><div>Location: Shanghai</div><div>Weather: Overcast, 23-30-27, AQI=2</div><div>Mood: 5-7-7</div><div>Summary: Friend meetup &amp; Instrument class</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Lunch with 王崴 and 孟祥雨 at a Japanese barbecue of 日月光. Xiangyu said that he sold his home in 2022 and bought a new home recently. The old home he sold was a very old apartment without elevator, with a total of 7 million. He bought a new condo at downtown for 14 million. The old home could only be sold for 4.5 million now and the condo would cost him 19 million back in 2022, so he thinks he saved 5 million. He is really courageous to buy such an expensive home now. I would hesitate so much for a 4.5 million home. Anyway, he&apos;s now looking for an audio designer to make his NBA game and asked us for resumes. I really don&apos;t know if he would be able to pay off all of his mortgage, good luck for him. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Just finished all my balance from 美餐. I am always able to not waste any resources upon deadline. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Had my last offline music classes. Took the vocal lesson first, tried to break through my barrier between real voice and falsetto, but still failed. I give up on voice class. I think my voice is not shapable anymore. Had the guitar class later. Learned Lumiere from Expedition 33. It&apos;s easier than I expected. Also played the violin at the music center for fun and showed my guitar teacher about the violin. I also drove him to Shanghai South Station to meet up with his girlfriend. We talked a lot about music careers on my car. </div></en-note>]]></content></note>
<note><title>2026/06/16 Tue</title><content><![CDATA[<en-note><div>Location: Shanghai</div><div>Weather: Drizzling, 22-25-23, AQI=1</div><div>Mood: 5-8-7</div><div>Summary: Friend meetup &amp; Weather software develop</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Lunch with 孙冠亚. Haven&apos;t seen him for so many years. He&apos;s more slim now, but not at his slimmest time. We ate in the same Thai restaurant where I visited last month. Food was still very nice but the portion of the meal for two was way too much. We still managed to finish them, but it made my afternoon feeling funky again. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Developed a weather history query and comparison software with Codex and OpenMeteo data source. It&apos;s a software that I wanted to do for so long! Vibe coding is so useful in such fields. It&apos;s just amazing that I can develop such a complicated software in half an hour!</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Dinner with 王雨谦 at a Yunnan cuisine near his company. After dinner he also took me to his office for a short visit. His boss has so many models, exhibiting in the office for such a large space. He has always been the only audio guy in his company so he is very free. He can even play games everyday morning. He has a private room for audio production, only sitting with an HR. Even his boss doesn&apos;t have a private room. Sometimes I also envy his work. The game he&apos;s making with Unreal meta sounds also seems very cool. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Had my last offline arranging class. Helped her to get a better string tracks using Kontatk built-in libraries. Spent a lot of time trying to figure out how Oray SunLogin could play audio on both host and client machines. I had to create virtual output devices in AudioMidiSettings on MacOS. </div></en-note>]]></content></note>
<note><title>2026/06/15 Mon</title><content><![CDATA[<en-note><div>Location: Hangzhou - Shanghai</div><div>Weather: Light Rain, 21-25-23, AQI=1</div><div>Mood: 4-5-5</div><div>Summary: Interview &amp; Gaming</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Had a diarrhea this morning. Had to go to gas station to shit right after leaving home. Couldn&apos;t recall what bad food I have eaten. Probably because last night I didn&apos;t put on quilt. Still feel uncomfortable all day even after had lunch of seafood noodles and a naan. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Interviewed another guy from PaperFold. He&apos;s a guy with nice potential, but might not fit Free Fire because he is very in favor of games made with Unreal Engine. We would still prefer 张圭书 to move on. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>QA found a bug that the follow emote&apos;s leader ID was not net broadcasted. From this bug we found another bug that the attenuation of move emotes are with emotes instead of footstep. More undos. Most of work we have done this version has been reverted. So disappointing!</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Played Sea of Remnants for more than 2 hours in the evening and accidentally fell asleep. When I woke up it&apos;s already 6 AM next day. </div></en-note>]]></content></note>
<note><title>2026/06/14 Sun</title><content><![CDATA[<en-note><div>Location: Hangzhou</div><div>Weather: Light Rain, 22-28-24, AQI=1</div><div>Mood: 5-5-6</div><div>Summary: Phone purchase</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Bought FF a new phone at 京东 offline store. We looked at both Oppo and Vivo. At similar price, Vivo has better camera, but the cameras are too large and the phone doesn&apos;t feel good on hand. So she still bought the Oppo new model. It costs 5100, still much more cost effective than iPhone despite DRAM price surge. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Moved some of my photos from phone to NAS. Tried a new photo tidying software called Tonfotos, but it&apos;s not that intuitive to use. I wrote a python script to organize the photos by filming date instead. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Played Brotato again and tried to unlock the two new characters. One is very hard to accomplish since one of the pets never shows up in the store. There&apos;s another character where only a single touch with enemy would kill him. It&apos;s really hard. We unlocked it by finishing a game under nightmare difficulty. Tried so many different character combinations and finally passed with Sailor, where all cool down of weapons could be instantly reset if getting a bounty. </div></en-note>]]></content></note>
<note><title>2026/06/13 Sat</title><content><![CDATA[<en-note><div>Location: Hangzhou</div><div>Weather: Medium Rain, 20-23-22, AQI=1</div><div>Mood: 6-6-6</div><div>Summary: Gym class</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Rainy day. Stayed at home and did my garden works. One of the pot broke into halves by itself so I moved it to a larger pot. Also moved some of my other plants to fit for better pot sizes. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Also assembled the baby bed. It&apos;s a bit tricky but we managed to do it without a draft. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>I was invited for a test gym class at the gym where I swim at. However the coach there kept talking with me, persuading me to buy classes, but not guiding me to do the exercises. He is such an old man who always praise himself but makes me reluctant. Left to go to supermarket before it closed. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>]]></content></note>
<note><title>2026/06/12 Fri</title><content><![CDATA[<en-note><div>Location: Shanghai - Hangzhou</div><div>Weather: Overcast, 23-31-26, AQI=2</div><div>Mood: 5-5-5</div><div>Summary: Guitar repair</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Sent my guitar to repair shop. The store owner made an inspection to my guitar and said it under very bad condition. The wood main plate is very distorted due to long time storage at high moisture environment and not loosing the strings. The tension of the strings could reach more than 70kg so the wood plate is bent. I would have to store the guitar there for two weeks, and pick it up again on my last day. I should pay more attention to the maintenance of all my instruments. They are very easy to get hard to use if I don&apos;t play it for a while. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Helped editing the resume for 毛瑞翔. He is looking for a QA job in game industry. Helped him to renovate all of his gaming experiences to fit better for the job. But I don&apos;t know if he can actually get an interview since his school and past work experience has no relation with the job. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Last day of OB54, still get a new bug today and fixed it. Making plans for the new version, though it&apos;s probably not my duty anymore.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>]]></content></note>
<note><title>2026/06/11 Thu</title><content><![CDATA[<en-note><div>Location: Shanghai</div><div>Weather: Partly Cloudy - Overcast, 22-32-26, AQI=2</div><div>Mood: 5-5-7</div><div>Summary: Dinner</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Finally done with all the bugs of OB54. I will not be submitting any more codes probably. That concludes my contributions to Garena. The remaining time I would be doing mostly document works. Also had the last biweekly meeting with tech audio guys. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Dinner with 刘佳. Haven&apos;t seen her for another two years. She&apos;s now working as a high school Chinese teacher, and her boyfriend is also a computer science teacher of the same school who is 3 years younger than her. We had dinner in a exquisite western restaurant where most customers are foreigners. Portions are small but tastes nice. Later we had yoghurts in another place and continued talking. We both envy each other&apos;s job. She envies my high salary, and I envy her vacant time. Life is like this, no one is satisfied with life completely. </div></en-note>]]></content></note>
<note><title>2026/06/10 Wed</title><content><![CDATA[<en-note><div>Location: Shanghai</div><div>Weather: Partly Cloudy, 21-30-24, AQI=1</div><div>Mood: 5-5-6</div><div>Summary: Bass class</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Had the last bass class at the new classroom. It&apos;s located in a much more crowded area. Parked in the wrong parking lot at first and finally found the place. It&apos;s a chain music education center with more than 10 campuses in Shanghai. The classrooms are well designed and sound proof. By charging my car for even 1 kWh, I can get free parking for 2 hours! The teacher brought me 5 tunes and I had time to play 4 of them. They include many different genres. I feel the teacher himself is not really good at it and I was basically self taught with only his guidance. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>]]></content></note>
<note><title>2026/06/09 Tue</title><content><![CDATA[<en-note><div>Location: Shanghai</div><div>Weather: Mostly Cloudy, 19-26-22, AQI=1</div><div>Mood: 5-5-6</div><div>Summary: Dinner</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Dinner with 顾玮琦. He is planning to leave Hypergryph, with two options. First is going to Alibaba in Guangzhou, leading a Three Kingdom cold weapon game like Mount &amp; Blade. Second is to make his own game, drawing investments. He says Arknight Endfield is now dropping very fast. He also thinks Sea of Remnants will be a success as long as it has multiplayer mode. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Finishing most of the bugs. Only some of the bugs that are hard to recreate are skipped. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>]]></content></note>
<note><title>2026/06/08 Mon</title><content><![CDATA[<en-note><div>Location: Hangzhou - Shanghai</div><div>Weather: Overcast, 21-23-20, AQI=1</div><div>Mood: 5-5-6</div><div>Summary: Bug fixing &amp; Arranging class</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Interviewed 张圭书 in the morning. The vibe was easy and we didn&apos;t ask any hard questions. Hope he can pass the second round tomorrow. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Still fixing emote related bugs. There are so many of them. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Weather is so cold today and windy. I didn&apos;t read the weather forecast and didn&apos;t bring any thick clothes. Have to run while outside. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Mostly doing velocity adjustment works for arranging class this evening. Still I think I am paid for arranging her songs. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>The music room I have been studying at is now out of rent. They merged with another existing music school.  So I moved all of my guitars and bass out. It&apos;s too hot to put in my car so I temporarily put them in my hotel room. Maybe my drum teacher will not be teaching music as his main career anymore. He once said he is making AI short films. </div></en-note>]]></content></note>
<note><title>2026/06/07 Sun</title><content><![CDATA[<en-note><div>Location: Hangzhou</div><div>Weather: Mostly Cloudy, 20-28-23, AQI=2</div><div>Mood: 7-6-8</div><div>Summary: Swimming &amp; Friend visit</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>林靖博 comes to Hangzhou to visit us. We bought many groceries at Sam this morning, preparing for a nice meal in the evening. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Went to swim before he came. It&apos;s weird that today I am really bad at swimming. Spent almost half an hour to get familiar with the movements again. Maybe because there are too many people in the swimming pool today and my swim route is always blocked. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>He drove his newly bought BMW 530i here. He&apos;s still very conservative and buys gas car. I took him around estate for a walk and he really enjoys our environment. Cooked steak, salmon, pork ribs and grilled tomatoes for dinner. He really appreciates my cooking skill. We played the board game 大宋百商图 after dinner, and I finally won it. Played some Steam co-op games later. Found a very nice and fun PvP game Fragmental. It&apos;s like Stick Fight where player is killed instantly. We also played Brotato. There&apos;s a new nightmare mode with two new characters. </div></en-note>]]></content></note>
<note><title>2026/06/06 Sat</title><content><![CDATA[<en-note><div>Location: Jiaxing - Hangzhou</div><div>Weather: Overcast - Light Rain, 20-24-21, AQI=1</div><div>Mood: 7-7-6</div><div>Summary: Countryside tour</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>It&apos;s my dad&apos;s birthday. The coincidence of four 6s in today only happens every 110 years. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Visited the botanical garden of Jiaxing in the morning. It&apos;s more of a natural park than manmade garden. It&apos;s very large that we only walked around a tiny portion of it. There&apos;s a greenhouse that sells plants. Bought a pruner, a vase and a philodendron plant. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Lunch at FF&apos;s colleague&apos;s house at a village. It&apos;s also her birthday. They made a big feast with so many dishes. Most of them tastes nice. Had a countryside tour after lunch around her village. The life there is really chill. Played 掼蛋 after getting back since it started to rain. I played with FF&apos;s leader against two of her friends. We first won a round and later lost all rounds. There&apos;s even a score tower that records the position for each pair of players. </div></en-note>]]></content></note>
<note><title>2026/06/05 Fri</title><content><![CDATA[<en-note><div>Location: Shanghai - Jiaxing</div><div>Weather: Mostly Cloudy, 21-29-24, AQI=1</div><div>Mood: 5-6-7</div><div>Summary: Team building</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Team building in the afternoon at a home party place in Aegean Sea Plaza. It&apos;s such a boring place with not much entertainments. There are only a few board games, and most of them are very common and primitive. There&apos;s only a Texas Hold&apos;em table but one of the card set have two missing cards. Played it for a while and left after I lost all the tokens. There are two console gaming rooms but none of us would like to play there, since we all have better devices at home. The only place where we were actually using was the mahjong table. The only drinks they have were soft drinks and water. We ordered KFC and that was the best part of the team building. Some of them went to a escape room downstairs. I didn&apos;t have enough time so I didn&apos;t go. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Drive to 嘉兴 to meet up with FF and her mom. Had dinner next to the hotel. It&apos;s a Southeastern Asia barbecue and cuisine. We ordered a few dishes and they are so delicious! The price was very reasonable. I am so surprised to find such authentic SEA cuisine in a small city. The owner looks like Malaysian. Hotel was nice and cheap. It&apos;s a three people room with free breakfast and only cost 240. </div></en-note>]]></content></note>
<note><title>2026/06/04 Thu</title><content><![CDATA[<en-note><div>Location: Shanghai</div><div>Weather: Overcast, 22-30-25, AQI=3</div><div>Mood: 5-4-6</div><div>Summary: Audio mixer optimization</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>The engine team says that the audio mixer changes we made this version made the lower end phones laggy. The audio thread takes similar time to render compared with the graphics thread. We dug deep into it and found that not only the duck volume or other DSP effects takes up lots of memory, but also anytime when a sound is sent to a bus, it has some static cost. On editor it only costs 2-3ms but on phone they said it&apos;s not acceptable. We have to revert our bus configurations in sound group table. Our footstep material was also reverted, so we almost didn&apos;t do any thing except for emotes this version. It&apos;s so disappointing. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Meeting of our entire sound department this afternoon. It&apos;s about AI tools. I didn&apos;t make any presentation but most people did. Honestly I don&apos;t trust AI that much now. The codes that 刘子阳 gives me are always too redundant. I&apos;d rather write by hand and only let AI review. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Different electric guitar class with teacher Huang. Practiced mostly solos today on multiple tunes. I found it much easier than playing barred chords. However my electric guitar strings are also tight and hard. Teacher says my guitar is more suitable for playing rhythmic section rather than melodic solos. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>NetEase HR says that I still need to transfer all my shares of my company out in order to be legally safe. I argued that it&apos;s very unlikely that no one in NetEase owns any companies, but she says it&apos;s the requirement. So I would have to transfer to mom anyway. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Our previously decided baby name 刘屿林 seems too used for the middle character. So we are thinking of different other characters to fill in. But me and FF both disagree on each other&apos;s ideas. Maybe we still fall back to original name anyway. </div></en-note>]]></content></note>
<note><title>2026/06/03 Wed</title><content><![CDATA[<en-note><div>Location: Shanghai</div><div>Weather: Medium Rain, 23-31-26, AQI=2</div><div>Mood: 5-5-6</div><div>Summary: Interview &amp; Guitar class</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Interviewed with 李光相, who worked at Perfect World on 幻塔 and 异环. He&apos;s a short and chubby guy which is very different from my expectation on looking. His fundamentals are good but he did less than I expected on the projects. We will let the programmer team to decide whether he matches our need. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Guitar class after work. Learned the electric guitar on a Reggae tune. The barred chords are so hard to play. Each time I press the index finger right, I couldn&apos;t press the other fingers hard enough, or vice versa. My wrist still hurts so I can&apos;t play for too long. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>My guitar amp was delivered on Monday but they still haven&apos;t received it. The company says I cannot deliverer it to the 丰巢柜, and have to let deliverer to withdraw it and put on rack instead. </div></en-note>]]></content></note>
<note><title>2026/06/02 Tue</title><content><![CDATA[<en-note><div>Location: Shanghai</div><div>Weather: Overcast, 24-32-27, AQI=2</div><div>Mood: 5-5-6</div><div>Summary: Dinner</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Dinner with 王崴 and 张圭书 at a new Thai restaurant nearby. Food was really nice but expensive. We were to persuade him to apply for our position. He says he has almost nothing to do at Lilith. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Back to work to fix remaining bugs. I broke the UGC audio system due to API changes. It&apos;s my last week of crunching and I will be basically free at Garena. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Played Sea of Remnants on my phone. The visual is much worse than on PC. Finished the first major boss of the map. The island exploration is not very interesting. I&apos;d rather have more activities in the sea. </div></en-note>]]></content></note>
<note><title>2026/06/01 Mon</title><content><![CDATA[<en-note><div>Location: Hangzhou - Shanghai</div><div>Weather: Overcast, 23-31-26, AQI=2</div><div>Mood: 5-5-8</div><div>Summary: Async optimization</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>My left wrist hurts so much after waking up today. Probably bent it while asleep. Not sure if I can still play instruments. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Finishing the JIRA tickets related to async loading optimizations. First tried to set all sounds to async load by default, but it was rejected. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Arranging class in the evening. I am focusing more back to music theory and ear trainings. She thinks so slowly about chord progressions and note positions, that she cannot understand what AI writes for her. The kids now are too relied on AI and becomes too lazy to do anything by themselves. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Went to a SPA on top of my music practice room. It&apos;s a Japanese style which is expensive, but the massager was pretty nice. She works as front desk of the mall and as massager at night. She&apos;s not very beautiful but has very smooth skin and body shape. She even did a breast massage and made me cum. Had a bath afterwards and it&apos;s 80 minutes in total. It&apos;s a cool experience but I probably wouldn&apos;t try again. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>]]></content></note>
</en-export>
